The paper deals with the development of high-performance sparse data structures and algorithms for arithmetic calculations involving numeric tensors. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), scientific computing (cs.SC), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on sparse data structures and algorithms, we believe that cs.DS and cs.NA are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SC, cs.SY, and cs.LG.
